<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Empty on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/empty/</link><description>Recent content in Empty on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/empty/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go SQL No Rows in Result Set Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sql-no-rows-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sql-no-rows-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-no-rows-in-result-set-fix"&gt;SQL No Rows in Result Set Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;sql: no rows in result set&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when &lt;code&gt;QueryRow.Scan&lt;/code&gt; is called but the query returned no rows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Go&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;database/sql&lt;/code&gt; package, &lt;code&gt;db.QueryRow&lt;/code&gt; returns a &lt;code&gt;*sql.Row&lt;/code&gt; that lazily executes the query. Calling &lt;code&gt;Scan&lt;/code&gt; on it triggers the query and attempts to read the first row. If the query returns no rows, &lt;code&gt;Scan&lt;/code&gt; returns &lt;code&gt;sql.ErrNoRows&lt;/code&gt;. This is not a bug — it&amp;rsquo;s a normal &amp;ldquo;not found&amp;rdquo; condition that must be handled.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Scala NoSuchElementException — Iterator or Collection Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/nosuchelement/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/scala/nosuchelement/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="nosuchelementexception--iterator-or-collection-error"&gt;NoSuchElementException — Iterator or Collection Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;NoSuchElementException&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you try to access an element that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist — typically calling &lt;code&gt;.next()&lt;/code&gt; on an exhausted iterator or &lt;code&gt;.head&lt;/code&gt; / &lt;code&gt;.last&lt;/code&gt; on an empty collection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Scala, &lt;code&gt;NoSuchElementException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you request an element from a collection or iterator that has no more elements. This is a common runtime error when working with streams, iterators, or collection methods that assume non-empty input.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>** (Enum.EmptyError) empty error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/enum-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/enum-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;Enum.EmptyError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you call a function on an empty enumerable that requires at least one element to work. Functions like &lt;code&gt;Enum.first/1&lt;/code&gt; with the &lt;code&gt;raise&lt;/code&gt; option or &lt;code&gt;Enum.min/1&lt;/code&gt; raise this error on empty collections.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;Enum.first/1&lt;/code&gt; or similar on an empty list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using functions that require at least one element without checking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing collections that may be empty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing empty-check before reduction operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Calling function that requires elements on empty list&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;min([])
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (Enum.EmptyError) empty error in Enum.min/1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Check if empty first or use default&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; [] &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;min(list)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or use Enum.min/2 with default&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;min([], &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Using first! on empty&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;first!([])
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (Enum.EmptyError)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use Enum.at/2 or Enum.take/2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;at([], &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;take([], &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# []&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;find([], &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; _ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Min of empty list&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;min([]) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (Enum.EmptyError) empty error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: First of empty list&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;first!([]) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (Enum.EmptyError)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Max of empty enumerable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Enum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;max(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MapSet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new()) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ** (Enum.EmptyError)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/function-clause"&gt;FunctionClauseError: no function clause matching&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/match-error"&gt;MatchError: no match of right hand side value&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>StateError: No element</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/state-error4/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/state-error4/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;StateError: No element&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you call &lt;code&gt;first&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;last&lt;/code&gt; on an empty iterable. These properties require at least one element to exist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling first/last on empty list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Filter returning no results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empty collection from database/API&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing empty check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Calling first on empty list
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; empty &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; [];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; first &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; empty.first; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// StateError: No element
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Check if empty first
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; empty &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; [];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (empty.isNotEmpty) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; first &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; empty.first;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Using first without checking
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; results &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list.where((x) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(results.first); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// StateError if no matches
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use firstWhere with orElse
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; results &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; list.where((x) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(results.firstWhere(
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; (x) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; orElse: () &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Empty list
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[].first; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// StateError: No element
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Empty after filter
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;].where((x) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;).first; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// StateError
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Empty set
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Set&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; emptySet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; {};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;emptySet.last; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// StateError: No element
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/range-error"&gt;RangeError: Index out of range&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/null-check-error"&gt;Null check operator used on null&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>